summary: An email from Jeffrey Epstein to an unidentified recipient discussing travel plans to New York City and requesting a place to stay. The document is part of the Epstein case files and is subject to a protective order.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: Jeffrey Epstein sends an email from Paris discussing his upcoming travel to New York City and requesting accommodation.

events.title: Epstein's planned NYC trip
events.description: Jeffrey Epstein plans to travel to New York City from Paris, arriving on a Thursday and leaving on a Monday, and requests a place to stay from the recipient.

keyFacts: Jeffrey Epstein was in Paris in May 2011 and planned to travel to New York City.
Epstein requested accommodation from an unidentified recipient during his NYC trip.
The document is subject to a protective order covering specific paragraphs (7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17).
